SLS 26RS-2600 ORIGINAL
2026 Regular Session
SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 130
BY SENATOR BOUDREAUX
COMMENDATIONS. Commends E. Joseph Savoie for his distinguished career in higher
education and extends best wishes upon the occasion of his well-deserved retirement.
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To commend Dr. E. Joseph Savoie for nearly five decades of exemplary public service,
3 visionary leadership, and extraordinary contributions to higher education in
4 Louisiana and to recognize his well-deserved retirement as president of the
5 University of Louisiana at Lafayette.
6 WHEREAS, Dr. E. Joseph Savoie, a native of Sulphur, Louisiana, has devoted his
7 life and career to advancing educational excellence, expanding opportunity, and
8 strengthening the future of Louisiana through higher education; and
9 WHEREAS, Dr. Savoie began his academic journey at the University of Louisiana
10 at Lafayette (UL Lafayette), where he earned both bachelor's and master's degrees, becoming
11 a proud two-time alumnus of the institution he would later lead to unprecedented levels of
12 achievement and national recognition; and
13 WHEREAS, his distinguished career in higher education began at UL Lafayette,
14 where he served with dedication and distinction in numerous leadership capacities, including
15 as its first vice president for University Advancement, executive director of the Alumni
16 Association, program director for the Union Program Council, student government adviser,
17 and adjunct assistant professor, demonstrating his exceptional ability to inspire students,
18 cultivate leadership, and advance institutional growth; and
