1 WHEREAS, after earning a doctorate in educational leadership and administration
2 from Teacher's College, Columbia University, Dr. Savoie was appointed in 1995 by
3 Governor-elect M.J. "Mike" Foster to serve on his higher education transition team and, in
4 1996, the Board of Regents selected Dr. Savoie to serve as interim commissioner of higher
5 education; and
6 WHEREAS, though initially intended to be temporary, Dr. Savoie's remarkable
7 leadership, strategic vision, and unwavering commitment to educational excellence quickly
8 earned the confidence and admiration of state leaders, prompting the Board of Regents to
9 appoint him permanently to the state's highest postsecondary education office; and
10 WHEREAS, Dr. Savoie served with extraordinary distinction as Louisiana
11 commissioner of higher education for twelve years under three gubernatorial
12 administrations, where he became widely respected as a consensus builder, reformer, and
13 champion for students and institutions across the state; and
14 WHEREAS, during his tenure as commissioner, Dr. Savoie played an instrumental
15 role in reshaping and modernizing Louisiana's higher education landscape through
16 transformative reforms, including restructuring higher education governance, creating the
17 Louisiana Community and Technical College System, strengthening teacher education
18 programs, securing full funding for the higher education formula, championing student
19 retention and completion in the wake of hurricanes Katrina and Rita, and establishing
20 Louisiana's first statewide needs-based financial aid program, thereby expanding educational
21 access and opportunity for countless students and families; and
22 WHEREAS, former Governor Kathleen Babineaux Blanco aptly described Dr.
23 Savoie as "the commissioner who has had the most positive influence on all of education in
24 Louisiana," reflecting the profound and lasting impact of his leadership upon the state's
25 educational system; and
26 WHEREAS, in 2008, following the retirement announcement of longtime UL
27 Lafayette President Dr. Ray P. Authement, Dr. Savoie sought the opportunity to return to his
28 alma mater and continue its legacy of excellence, bringing with him unmatched statewide
29 experience, national perspective, and a deep and abiding love for UL Lafayette; and
30 WHEREAS, the University of Louisiana System Board of Supervisors selected Dr.
