1 Savoie to serve as UL Lafayette's sixth president, and on July 2, 2008, he began a historic
2 tenure defined by innovation, strategic growth, academic excellence, and transformational
3 achievement; and
4 WHEREAS, under Dr. Savoie's visionary leadership, UL Lafayette experienced
5 unprecedented advancement and emerged as one of the nation's premier public research
6 universities, earning the prestigious Carnegie R1 classification and placing UL Lafayette
7 among the top tier of research institutions in the United States; and
8 WHEREAS, during his presidency, Dr. Savoie led transformative investments in
9 research and development, resulting in research expenditures increasing by nearly two
10 hundred percent between 2014 and 2021, while also overseeing significant campus
11 expansion and modernization through the construction of new academic buildings, residence
12 halls, research laboratories, athletic and student-centered facilities, as well as the acquisition
13 and development of UL Lafayette's Health Sciences Campus; and
14 WHEREAS, Dr. Savoie championed academic innovation and workforce
15 development through the expansion of undergraduate and graduate degree programs
16 designed to meet the evolving needs of Louisiana's economy and global society, while also
17 fostering stronger partnerships between UL Lafayette and the surrounding community; and
18 WHEREAS, in the years following 2020, UL Lafayette achieved record enrollment
19 in undergraduate and graduate programs, reflecting the growing national reputation of the
20 institution and the success of Dr. Savoie's steadfast commitment to student achievement,
21 academic excellence, and institutional advancement; and
22 WHEREAS, Dr. Savoie devoted thirty-five years of service to the University of
23 Louisiana at Lafayette, including seventeen transformative years as president, and in
24 recognition of his extraordinary leadership, enduring contributions, and unwavering
25 dedication to the institution, the University of Louisiana System Board of Supervisors
26 conferred upon him the title of president emeritus upon his retirement; and
27 WHEREAS, throughout his distinguished career, Dr. E. Joseph Savoie has
28 exemplified integrity, humility, wisdom, and servant leadership, leaving an indelible mark
29 upon higher education in Louisiana and inspiring generations of students, educators,
30 administrators, and public servants through his tireless dedication and extraordinary
